            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Meet",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "遇见，结识"
          },
          {
            "word": "At",
            "pos": "prep.",
            "meaning": "在...（小地点/时刻）"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Even if one didn't know from concrete examples (the 1936 Olympic Games, for instance) that international sporting contests lead to orgies of hatred, one could deduce it from general principles.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 30.32,
      "endTime": 45.52,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Nearly all the sports practised nowadays are competitive.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 45.53,
      "endTime": 49.39,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "are",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "You play to win, and the game has little meaning unless you do your utmost to win.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 49.4,
      "endTime": 55.65,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
